        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Alternative Resolution: Rabbi Yochanan ben Nuri's Appearance-Based Standard",
      "display_title": "Appearance & Taste",
      "timestamp": "17:05",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "The mishnah from Mikva'ot about water and milk: three log of water missing a tiny amount plus milk",
          "display_title": "Water-Milk Mixture",
          "timestamp": "17:05"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yochanan ben Nuri's principle: identity determined by appearance, not actual composition",
          "display_title": "Rav's Position",
          "timestamp": "20:47"
        },
        {
          "title": "The Gemara's expansion: appearance and taste both determine identity according to Rabbi Yochanan ben Nuri",
          "display_title": "Appearance & Taste",
          "timestamp": "22:02"
        },
        {
          "title": "Applying Rabbi Yochanan ben Nuri to metamed: still tastes and appears as water, so it is water",
          "display_title": "Applied to Metamed",
          "timestamp": "25:02"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Rabbi Elazar's Objection: The Debate Occurs Before Fermentation, Not After",
      "display_title": "Rabbi Elazar",
      "timestamp": "29:22",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Elazar argues the debate in Maasrot occurs when it has not yet fermented",
          "display_title": "Before Fermentation",
          "timestamp": "29:22"
        },
        {
          "title": "Explanation: even Rabbi Yehuda's obligation to tithe is only rabbinic, not full wine status",
          "display_title": "Rabbinic Status",
          "timestamp": "30:32"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Practical Application: Metamed's Status for Mikvah Purification",
      "display_title": "Mikvah Application",
      "timestamp": "34:07",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Baraita: metamed before fermentation can be brought into a mikvah; after fermentation it cannot",
          "display_title": "Metamed Mikvah",
          "timestamp": "34:07"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rava's qualification: only when originally pure water became tamei; not for originally tamei water",
          "display_title": "Pure Water Only",
          "timestamp": "35:54"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Ashi's challenge: why the distinction between originally pure and originally tamei water",
          "display_title": "Rav Ashi's Q",
          "timestamp": "36:44"
        },
        {
          "title": "Resolution: wine floats above water; only wine touches mikvah water, causing problem; solution is to stir",
          "display_title": "Density Separation",
          "timestamp": "37:04"
        }
      ]
    },
